Module com.example.flashcardai
Package db

Class Flashcard

java.lang.Object
db.Flashcard
public class Flashcard extends Object
Model class representing a flashcard. Flashcards belong to a deck and include learning content along with spaced repetition metadata.

Supports both text and media formats, and stores difficulty and usage metrics to enable adaptive learning via spaced repetition.

  • Constructor Details

    • Flashcard

      public Flashcard(int id, int deckId, String front, String back, String mediaType, String difficulty, String createdAt, String imagePath, int repetitions, double easinessFactor, String lastReviewedAt, String nextReviewAt)
      Constructs a Flashcard with all properties.
      Parameters:
      id - the ID of the flashcard
      deckId - the ID of the associated deck
      front - the front (question/prompt) text
      back - the back (answer/explanation) text
      mediaType - the type of media used ("text", "image", etc.)
      difficulty - the difficulty level of the flashcard
      createdAt - timestamp of when the flashcard was created
      imagePath - path to the image file, if applicable
      repetitions - how many times the card has been reviewed
      easinessFactor - SuperMemo easiness factor used in spaced repetition
      lastReviewedAt - timestamp of last review
      nextReviewAt - timestamp of next recommended review
